---
import MadeByKaj from '../components/MadeByKaj.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';

const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const explorePath = `${basePath}explore/`;
const constellationFlyThroughPath = `${basePath}explore/constellations-and-3d-space/`;
const parallaxPath = `${basePath}explore/parallax/`;
const learnPath = `${basePath}learn/`;
const hrDiagramPath = `${basePath}learn/topic/hr-diagram/`;
const aboutPath = `${basePath}about/`;
---

<Layout
	title="Found in Space"
	description="Explore the stars near the Sun through guided journeys, clear explanations, and open technical notes built on measurements from ESA's Gaia mission."
>
	<SiteHeader />

	<main class="page">
		<section class="hero">
			<p class="eyebrow">A guide to the stars near the Sun</p>
			<h1>Start with the night sky you know. Discover the space it hides.</h1>
			<p class="intro">
				Found in Space is a growing home for exploring the solar neighbourhood: the stars nearest
				to our Sun. Using measurements from ESA's Gaia mission, it turns catalogues and
				visualisations into guided journeys, clear explanations, and tools people can actually
				learn from.
			</p>
			<div class="hero__actions">
				<a class="button button--primary" href={explorePath}>Take a first look</a>
				<a class="button button--ghost" href="#build">How it's built</a>
			</div>
			<div class="hero__note">
				<p>
					Still early, but already taking shape as part exhibit, part classroom, part lab.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section-grid" aria-label="Choose your path">
			<article class="panel panel--accent" id="explore">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Explore</p>
				<h2>Follow guided journeys from familiar skies into depth, distance, and scale.</h2>
				<p>
					Start with constellations, bright stars, and recognisable patterns, then see what
					changes when those same stars are placed in three-dimensional space.
				</p>
				<div class="panel__feature">
					<p class="panel__feature-label">Now live</p>
					<h3>Constellation fly-through</h3>
					<p>
						Begin with Orion, keep the familiar shape in view, and move through the local stars
						until the flat pattern starts to open into depth.
					</p>
					<a class="panel__link" href={explorePath}>Go to Explore</a>
					<a class="panel__link panel__link--secondary" href={constellationFlyThroughPath}>Jump to: Orion fly-through →</a>
				</div>
			</article>
			<article class="panel" id="learn">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Learn</p>
				<h2>Turn curiosity into understanding with clear explainers and guided lessons.</h2>
				<p>
					For self-directed learners, students, and educators who want more than a pretty
					simulation: plain-language concepts grounded in real data.
				</p>
				<div class="panel__feature">
					<p class="panel__feature-label">First lesson</p>
					<h3>The Hertzsprung-Russell diagram</h3>
					<p>
						One of astronomy's most powerful maps — plot temperature against luminosity and watch
						the structure of the stellar population emerge from real Gaia data.
					</p>
					<a class="panel__link" href={hrDiagramPath}>Open the HR diagram</a>
				</div>
			</article>
			<article class="panel" id="build">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Build</p>
				<h2>See how astronomical measurements become something you can explore in a browser.</h2>
				<p>
					Behind the scenes are source catalogues, data cleaning, spatial indexing, and a
					browser-based viewer. The technical side will stay open, inspectable, and explained in
					human terms.
				</p>
				<div class="panel__feature">
					<p class="panel__feature-label">The dataset</p>
					<h3>Over a billion stars in 3D space</h3>
					<p>
						Real distance measurements from ESA's Gaia spacecraft, combined with the
						Hipparcos survey — merged into a single navigable dataset. All open source.
					</p>
					<a class="panel__link" href={`${basePath}build/`}>Read the technical notes</a>
				</div>
			</article>
		</section>

		<section class="story">
			<div class="story__lead">
				<p class="eyebrow">Why this project exists</p>
				<h2>Wonder is a great starting point, but it should lead somewhere.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="story__body">
				<p>
					Most people meet astronomy through images, headlines, or the visible sky. That first
					spark matters. Found in Space is about carrying it further: helping people move from
					"that's beautiful" to "I understand what I'm looking at."
				</p>
				<p>
					The solar neighbourhood is a good place to begin because scale becomes easier to feel when
					it starts close to home. From there we can talk honestly about distance, measurement,
					structure, and uncertainty without losing the sense of wonder that brought people here in
					the first place.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="bands">
			<article class="band">
				<p class="band__label">Featured explore</p>
				<h3>What constellations hide about 3D space</h3>
				<p>
					A familiar pattern in the night sky becomes an entry point for perspective, parallax, and
					the fact that stars which look adjacent from Earth may be separated by huge distances.
				</p>
				<p class="band__link">
					<a href={constellationFlyThroughPath}>Start with the Orion fly-through</a>
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="band">
				<p class="band__label">Featured lesson</p>
				<h3>The HR diagram: a map of stellar physics</h3>
				<p>
					Plot temperature against luminosity for the stars around the Sun and watch the main
					sequence, white dwarfs, and stellar populations emerge from real Gaia data.
				</p>
				<p class="band__link">
					<a href={hrDiagramPath}>Open the HR diagram lesson</a>
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>

		<section class="about" id="about">
			<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
			<h2>Teaching through data. Learning through wonder.</h2>
			<p>
				Found in Space exists because data is a wonderful way to learn about the universe, and
				the universe is a wonderful way to learn about data. It takes real astronomical
				measurements, shares the entire process of turning them into something explorable, and
				uses what emerges to teach — asking questions as often as it provides answers.
			</p>
			<p class="about__link">
				<a href={aboutPath}>Read more about the project</a>
			</p>
		</section>

		<MadeByKaj />
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page {
		position: relative;
		min-height: 100vh;
		padding-top: 3.5rem;
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 4.2rem 0 2.4rem;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	h3 {
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.25rem);
		line-height: 0.95;
		max-width: 12ch;
	}

	.intro {
		max-width: 46rem;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
		margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
	}

	.hero__actions {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.85rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.button--primary {
		box-shadow: 0 16px 30px rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.18);
	}

	.button--ghost {
		background: rgba(9, 18, 33, 0.5);
	}

	.hero__note {
		background: var(--fis-panel);
		border: 1px solid rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.16);
		border-radius: var(--fis-radius);
		backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
		box-shadow: var(--fis-shadow);
		max-width: 36rem;
		padding: 1.05rem 1.15rem;
	}

	.section-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 2rem 0 4rem;
	}

	.panel__feature {
		margin-top: 1.4rem;
		padding-top: 1.15rem;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.12);
	}

	.panel__feature-label {
		margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.14em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-blue);
	}

	.panel__link,
	.band__link a {
		color: var(--fis-gold);
		text-decoration-color: rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.42);
	}

	.panel__link--secondary {
		display: block;
		margin-top: 0.6rem;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		opacity: 0.75;
	}

	.band__label {
		margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	.story {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		align-items: start;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.story__lead h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
		line-height: 1.02;
		max-width: 11ch;
	}

	.story__body {
		padding-top: 0.35rem;
	}

	.bands {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.band {
		padding: 1.45rem;
		background: var(--fis-panel-strong);
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line);
		border-radius: var(--fis-radius);
		backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
		box-shadow: var(--fis-shadow);
	}

	.band__link {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.about {
		background: var(--fis-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line);
		border-radius: var(--fis-radius);
		backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
		box-shadow: var(--fis-shadow);
		padding: 1.6rem;
		max-width: 48rem;
	}

	h2 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1.75rem;
		line-height: 1.1;
	}

	h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		line-height: 1.15;
	}

	p {
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
	}

	section p + p {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.about a {
		color: var(--fis-gold);
		text-decoration-color: rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.46);
	}

	.about__link {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.section-grid,
		.story,
		.bands {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.story__lead h2 {
			max-width: none;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.page {
			padding-top: 2.25rem;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 14vw, 4.2rem);
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.intro {
			font-size: 1.05rem;
		}
	}
</style>
